Package uk.ac.manchester.spinnaker.messages.scp

The messages of SpiNNaker Control Protocol (SCP).
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CommandCode
    All command codes usable in SCP-like messages.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ApplicationRun
    An SCP request to run an application.
    ApplicationStop
    An SCP Request to stop an application.
    CheckOKResponse
    An SCP response to a request which returns nothing other than OK or an error.
    ClearIOBUF
    An SCP Request to clear the IOBUF on a core.
    ClearReinjectionQueue
    An SCP Request to set the dropped packet reinjected packet types.
    CountState
    An SCP Request to get a count of the cores in a particular state.
    CountState.Response
    An SCP response to a request for the number of cores in a given state.
    FECRequest<T extends SCPResponse>
    A command message to a core using FrontEndCommon lib's simulation management subsystem.
    FillRequest
    An SCP request to fill a region of memory on a chip with repeated words of data.
    FixedRouteInitialise
    Sets a fixed route entry.
    FixedRouteRead
    Gets a fixed route entry.
    FixedRouteRead.Response
    Response for the fixed route read.
    FloodFillData
    An SCP request to flood fill some data.
    FloodFillEnd
    An SCP request to finish a flood fill of data across all cores and launch the application.
    FloodFillStart
    An SCP request to start a flood fill of data.
    GetChipInfo
    An SCP request to read the chip information from a core.
    GetChipInfo.Response
    An SCP response to a request for the version of software running.
    GetReinjectionStatus
    An SCP Request to get the status of the dropped packet reinjection.
    GetReinjectionStatus.Response
    An SCP response to a request for the dropped packet reinjection status.
    GetVersion
    An SCP request to read the version of software running on a core.
    GetVersion.Response
    An SCP response to a request for the version of software running.
    IPTagClear
    An SCP Request to clear an IP Tag.
    IPTagGet
    An SCP Request to get an IP tag.
    IPTagGet.Response
    An SCP response to a request for an IP tags.
    IPTagGet.TagDescription
    Description of a tag.
    IPTagGetInfo
    An SCP Request information about IP tags.
    IPTagGetInfo.Response
    An SCP response to a request for information about IP tags.
    IPTagGetInfo.TagInfo  
    IPTagSet
    An SCP Request to set a (forward) IP Tag.
    IPTagSetTTO
    An SCP request to set the transient timeout for future SCP requests.
    LoadApplicationRoutes
    An SDP Request to load the previously-saved application multicast router table.
    LoadSystemRoutes
    An SDP Request to load the previously-configured system multicast router table.
    NoResponse
    An SCP response that should never be received because its request is guaranteed to be a one-way request.
    PayloadedResponse<T,​E extends Exception>
    A response that holds a payload.
    ReadLink
    An SCP request to read a region of memory via a link on a chip.
    ReadLink.Response
    An SCP response to a request to read a region of memory via a link on a chip.
    ReadMemory
    An SCP request to read a region of memory.
    ReadMemory.Response
    An SCP response to a request to read a region of memory on a chip.
    ReinjectorRequest<T extends CheckOKResponse>
    A command message to an extra monitor control core to manipulate the packet reinjection subsystem.
    ResetReinjectionCounters
    An SCP Request to reset the statistics counters of the dropped packet reinjection.
    ReverseIPTagSet
    An SCP Request to set a Reverse IP Tag.
    RouterAlloc
    An SCP Request to allocate space for routing entries.
    RouterClear
    An SCP request to clear the router on a chip.
    RouterInit
    A request to initialise the router on a chip.
    RouterTableRequest
    A command message to an extra monitor control core to manipulate the router table.
    SaveApplicationRoutes
    An SDP Request to save the currently-installed application multicast router table.
    SCPRequest<T extends SCPResponse>
    Represents an Abstract SCP Request.
    SCPRequestHeader
    Represents the header of an SCP Request.
    SCPResponse
    Represents an abstract SCP response.
    SCPResultMessage
    The low-level format of SCP result message.
    SDRAMAlloc
    An SCP Request to allocate space in the SDRAM space.
    SDRAMDeAlloc
    An SCP Request to free space in the SDRAM.
    SendSignal
    An SCP Request to send a signal to cores.
    SequenceNumberSource
    Where to get sequence numbers from.
    SetLED
    An SCP request to change the state of an LED.
    SetReinjectionPacketTypes
    An SCP Request to set the dropped packet reinjected packet types.
    SetRouterEmergencyTimeout
    An SCP Request to set the router emergency timeout for dropped packet reinjection.
    SetRouterTimeout
    An SCP Request to the extra monitor core to set the router timeout for dropped packet reinjection.
    UpdateProvenanceAndExit
    An SCP Request to update the runtime info on a core.
    UpdateRuntime
    An SCP Request to update the runtime info on a core.
    WriteLink
    A request to write memory on a neighbouring chip.
    WriteMemory
    A request to write memory on a chip.
